d in scholarly evaluations of the writer's work. Employing a partly chronological, partly thematic scheme, Mahalel follows Peretz's radicalism from its inception and then through the various ways in which it was synchronically expressed during this intense period of history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 4aGeneral Interest : Biography. 4aHistory : Radical History. 4aJewish Studies : Jewish Studies. 4aLiterature : Hebrew Language and Literature. 4aLiterature : Literary History. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Jewish.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2023z978311149193640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143849234640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438492346423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438492346/original  a978-3-11-149193-6  SUNY Press eBook Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles